	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Two random unrelated thoughts:<br /><br />1- The MSP430, while designed to be useful to a C compiler, is actually a pretty fun ISA to just work with anyway<br /><br />2- <a href="https://media.ccc.de/search?q=Natalie+Silvanovich" class="postlink">Natalie Silvanovich</a> has code-injection attacks working on at least some models of Tamagotchis, which we know are running on the Sunplus 6502 variant.

		

