		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">lidnariq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">2- <a href="https://media.ccc.de/search?q=Natalie+Silvanovich" class="postlink">Natalie Silvanovich</a> has code-injection attacks working on at least some models of Tamagotchis, which we know are running on the Sunplus 6502 variant.</div>Yes, that, and the keychain photoframe hack, was how I learnt of 6502 CPU cores existing, embedded in really small devices.  I was dreaming about finding/using such a core, and was wondering if anybody knew if they were available / usable in a watch.<br /><br />A programmable watch in a <em>slim</em> (Databank / Casio calculator) formfactor would be desirable, I think. G-Shocks are grotesque &amp; overly thick, and Tamagotchis on a wrist would be so too.

		

